content.problem:
Find the area of the L-shaped figure shown below.

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.5]

 (0,0) – (8,0) – (8,3) – (3,3) – (3,6) – (0,6) – cycle;

 % Dimensions
 at (4,0) {8};
 at (8,1.5) {3};
 at (5.5,3) {5};
 at (3,4.5) {3};
 at (1.5,6) {3};
 at (0,3) {6};
tikzpicture
center

content.solution:
**Method 1 (Addition):** Divide into two rectangles.

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.4]

 (0,0) – (8,0) – (8,3) – (0,3) – cycle;

 (0,3) – (3,3) – (3,6) – (0,6) – cycle;
 (0,3) – (8,3);
 at (4,1.5) {$8 \times 3 = 24$};
 at (1.5,4.5) {$3 \times 3 = 9$};
tikzpicture
center
\[
 A = 24 + 9 = 33 \text{ square units}
\]

**Method 2 (Subtraction):** Start with a large rectangle, 
subtract the missing corner.

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.4]

 (0,0) rectangle (8,6);
 ll[white] (3,3) rectangle (8,6);
 (3,3) rectangle (8,6);
 at (2,3) {$8 \times 6$};
 at (5.5,4.5) {$5 \times 3$};
tikzpicture
center
\[
 A = (8 \times 6) - (5 \times 3) = 48 - 15 = 33 \text{ square units}
\]

Both methods give the same answer: $A = 33$.

